Protons have a positive charge, while neutrons have no charge. Electrons are found in the electron cloud, which is the area around the nucleus. Electrons have a negative charge. The number of protons in an atom determines the element of an atom, and the number of neutrons determines the isotope of an atom. The number of electrons in an atom determines the charge of the atom. If an atom has an equal number of protons and electrons, it is neutral. If an atom has more protons than electrons, it is positively charged. If an atom has more electrons than protons, it is negatively charged.

As she sat at her desk, staring blankly at the computer screen in front of her, Emily felt a sense of unease wash over her. She had been working as a marketing specialist for five years, and while she had enjoyed the fast-paced and creative environment, she couldn't shake the feeling that it was time for a change. The problem was, she had no idea what she wanted to do instead.
Emily's boss, Rachel, had just called her into her office to discuss a promotion. The catch was that the promotion would require Emily to relocate to the company's headquarters in another state, which would mean leaving behind her friends, family, and the comfortable routine she had established in her current city. On the other hand, if she turned down the promotion, she would be giving up a significant raise and a chance to take on more responsibility in her career.
As Emily weighed her options, she couldn't help but think about all the things she had always wanted to do but never had the time for. She had always been passionate about photography, and had even taken a few courses in college. She had also always been interested in sustainability and had volunteered for several environmental organizations in her free time. But how could she possibly make a career out of these interests?
Just as Emily was starting to feel overwhelmed, her phone rang. It was her best friend, Sarah, calling to check in. Emily filled her in on the situation with the promotion, and Sarah listened attentively before offering her opinion. "You have to do what's best for you, Em," she said. "But if you're feeling stuck, maybe it's time to take a leap of faith and try something new. You're not getting any younger, and you never know what opportunities might come your way if you take a chance."
Emily thought about Sarah's words as she hung up the phone. She realized that she had been so focused on the security and stability of her current job that she had forgotten to think about what truly made her happy. She thought about all the times she had taken her camera with her on hikes and trips, capturing the beauty of the world around her. She thought about the sense of fulfillment she had felt when she was volunteering for environmental causes.
As she sat there, a sense of clarity began to wash over her. She knew what she had to do. She picked up the phone and dialed Rachel's number, her heart pounding in her chest. "Rachel, I appreciate the offer, but I'm going to have to turn it down," she said, trying to sound confident. "I'm going to take some time to figure out what I really want to do with my career, and I think that means taking a risk and trying something new."
As she hung up the phone, Emily felt a weight lift off her shoulders. She knew that she had made the right decision, and that the uncertainty of the future was actually a thrilling prospect. She took a deep breath, feeling a sense of excitement and anticipation wash over her. She was ready to take the leap and see where her career would take her next.

Step 1: Download and Install Blender
First, you need to download and install Blender from the official website. Once installed, launch the software and create a new project by clicking on "File" > "New" > "Blank Project".
Step 2: Create a New Scene
In the new project, create a new scene by clicking on "File" > "New" > "Scene". Name the scene "House".
Step 3: Create a New Mesh
In the "Object Mode", click on "Shift + A" to create a new mesh. Select "Mesh" > "Cube" to create a cube. This will be the base of our house.
Step 4: Extrude the Cube
Select the cube and press "E" to extrude it. This will create a new face on the cube. Move the cursor to the top of the cube and click to create a new face.
Step 5: Create a Roof
Select the top face of the cube and press "Ctrl + R" to create a new edge loop. Move the cursor to the center of the face and click to create a new edge loop. This will create a new face on the top of the cube, which will be the roof.
Step 6: Add Windows and Doors
Select the front face of the cube and press "Ctrl + R" to create a new edge loop. Move the cursor to the center of the face and click to create a new edge loop. This will create a new face on the front of the cube, which will be the door. Repeat this process to create windows on the sides of the cube.
Step 7: Add a Floor
Select the bottom face of the cube and press "E" to extrude it. This will create a new face on the bottom of the cube, which will be the floor.
Step 8: Add a Back Wall
Select the back face of the cube and press "E" to extrude it. This will create a new face on the back of the cube, which will be the back wall.
Step 9: Add a Front Wall
Select the front face of the cube and press "E" to extrude it. This will create a new face on the front of the cube, which will be the front wall.
Step 10: Add a Siding
Select the entire cube and press "Ctrl + Shift + R" to create a new edge loop. Move the cursor to the center of the cube and click to create a new edge loop. This will create a new face on the cube, which will be the siding.
Step 11: Add a Texture
Select the siding face and press "Shift + D" to duplicate it. Move the cursor to the center of the cube and click to create a new face. This will create a new texture on the siding.
Step 12: Render the Scene
Click on "Render Layers" > "Render" to render the scene. You can adjust the render settings to your liking.
Step 13: Save the Render
Once the render is complete, click on "File" > "Save As" to save the render as an image file.
